// Copy this file to Plaid.local.xcconfig (gitignored) and fill in real values
// from your Plaid dashboard (https://dashboard.plaid.com/team-settings/keys).
// Config/Plaid.xcconfig (committed, safe placeholder defaults) #includes this
// file when it's present, so its assignments override the placeholders —
// see that file for the full explanation.
//
// PLAID_CLIENT_ID is a single value shared across Plaid's Sandbox and
// Production environments (Plaid's own account model) — only the secret
// differs per environment, hence PLAID_SANDBOX_SECRET and
// PLAID_PRODUCTION_SECRET below. PLAID_PRODUCTION_SECRET is only needed once
// you're ready to link a real account in Production via the in-app
// Sandbox/Production toggle (reservoir-adq.6.2) — leave it blank/placeholder
// until then; the app defaults to Sandbox and stays there until you flip the
// toggle (with its confirmation step) yourself.
//
// OAuth-institution redirects use a universal link
// (https://johnpease.github.io/oauth), not a custom URL scheme — Plaid's
// dashboard requires an https redirect URI. The domain is hardcoded in
// PlaidServiceLive.swift and must be registered as an "Allowed redirect
// URI" in the Plaid dashboard, and its Associated Domains entitlement
// (Reservoir.entitlements) must list the same host. No per-developer
// config needed here.
//
// These values are embedded into the built app's Info.plist and are
// readable by anyone with the .app bundle — acceptable only under this
// app's accepted risk posture (personal, sideloaded, single-user, not
// distributed). Do not commit Plaid.local.xcconfig.

PLAID_CLIENT_ID = your_plaid_client_id
PLAID_SANDBOX_SECRET = your_plaid_sandbox_secret
PLAID_PRODUCTION_SECRET = your_plaid_production_secret
